2023_description: Opti is a technology company that enables communities and businesses to continuously improve stormwater management by delivering real-time visibility, adaptively controlling assets, and supporting smart city initiatives. For infrastructure owners, Opti reduces operating and capital costs, enables environmental compliance, and reduces risk from volatile environmental conditions and uncertain future growth.
2018_description:
OptiRTC (Opti) is a technology company that delivers Software-as-a-Service solutions to optimize the function of civil and environmental infrastructure. Opti's primary focus is the intelligent control of stormwater in urban environments.

Opti was built to be the highest value and most easily deployable stormwater management solution. We work with municipalities, private landowners, and large corporations on retrofits and new construction to make infrastructure intelligent and address pressing environmental issues.

The Opti Platform integrates network and microcontroller hardware with sensors, valves, relays, and infinitely scalable cloud services to deliver reliable information services to water infrastructure professionals. Opti leverages open internet standards to deliver secure information access to web dashboards and secure control of distributed infrastructure.

Opti was built to be as effective at thousands of distributed sites as it is on a single deployment. The advantage of cloud-native technology is the ability to seamlessly and securely control and monitor millions of sites from a single web dashboard. 

Opti dynamically controls stormwater infrastructure to limit wet-weather discharges to combined sewers, improve water quality, reduce flooding, and reuse stormwater.

2023_description: Rally is Mass Mobility as a Service: technology and model innovations for the business of buses. With millions of rides completed, Rally is disrupting the mode of transportation that moves more people than any other. Our AI creates new intercity routes for regional transport and our crowdfunding/sourcing marketplace facilitates surge demand for travel during peak times or mass movements. Rally converts private car users to shared bus riders, unlocking the value of the underutilized assets of the bus industry. While Rally introduces bus travel to many first-time riders, our platform also provides traditional bus charter customers the digital tools to manage their entire journey, from route planning and procurement to marketing automation, payments and customer service.
2018_description:
Events bring people together. We think they should get there together, too. 

Rally is crowdpowered travel. Our technology connects people who are going to the same place, then delivers high-end buses to get them there and back. Choose from preset trips to popular events and destinations — or set up your own trip, share it with friends, and publish it to the rest of our riders.

This isn’t a new idea: for centuries, people have been going better by going together. Together is easier, more comfortable, and more fun. It’s better for the community, the economy, and the planet. It just makes sense.

We’re headquartered in New York City, and we’ve helped more than 600,000 people in 3,000 cities in North America get to events and destinations.

Our mission is to maximize the business and impact opportunities professional athletes are passionate about while at the same time transform the current inefficient, fragmented, costly, and often predatory retainer and debt services commonly offered to athletes prior to receiving their first paycheck.    360 first engages with athletes in the form of a pro athlete business accelerator in 3 phases of growth. We are projected to file up to 20 Reg A offerings in 2021 for up to $75 million each. 2023_description: Bright.md is a developer of an AI-powered virtual-care platform designed to modernize direct-to-patient telehealth for healthcare systems. The company partners with premier healthcare organizations to offer SmartExam to more than 10 million patients who are seeking convenient urgent and primary care online, connecting them to their physicians via a home computer or mobile device reducing visits, enabling patients to receive conveniently, high quality, asynchronous, online care from established and trusted health system providers. The company was founded in 2014 and is based in Portland, Oregon.
2018_description:
Bright.md’s SmartExam is a virtual physician assistant that helps primary care groups automate up to 90% of provider time spent on low-acuity conditions, such as colds, flu, and earaches, that often make up more than half of their visit volume.

Instead of scheduling an office visit, providers send patients online to complete an evidence based, dynamic and adaptive clinical interview on their mobile device or home computer. Patient responses are processed into a highly efficient format, including automated chart-ready documentation (personalized to each patient's interview), and evidence based treatment recommendations. That means that diagnosis, treatment & documentation by the patient's doctor now take less than 2 minutes of time. When finished, notes go automatically to the provider's EMR, prescriptions go to patient's pharmacy of choice, and patients get an electronic AVS, and scheduled follow-up messaging to ensure that they are improving as expected.

SmartExam reduces the time spent on the low-acuity conditions, such as colds, flus and earaches by up to 90%.  Because these types of conditions can make up as much as half of Primary Care visit volumes, this approach can expand medical group capacity by 30%, reduce incremental visit costs by 80%, and grow total margin by up to 3x for provider groups.

That level of reduced visit costs make care dramatically more affordable for patients and payers, while still improving margins for providers, and increasing their efficiency by an order of magnitude. All this happens through a beautiful online tool, that delights providers and patients, without the patient ever having to come into their doctor’s office.

2023_description: MedAware Systems solved the problem of making the vast and chaotic body of medical science research data instantly accessible. The Company provides its Science of Health Informatics (SOHInfo) subscription service to Pharma and medical device companies and will soon expand to payers. It utilizes a combination of Human and Artificial Intelligence to make the vast body of clinical data instantly available and indispensable for fully understanding the safety and efficacy of medical treatments and devices. Its SOHInfo service provides all available evidence from clinical trials research to certify the efficacy and safety of drugs, devices, or other therapies (for example, CER, 505(b)(2), and 510K filings); optimize due diligence; create powerful, evidence-based competitive analysis and marketing messaging; and thoroughly understand prior research before designing new clinical trials or creating new drugs or devices. MedAware Systems databases contain all available data from published medical science research for various disease/condition areas. This massive amount of data can be analyzed in seconds. Users are able to filter and query the data however they choose in order to answer specific questions such as which treatments show the best outcome for particular cohorts, or how does drug or device x compare to drug or device with respect to various outcomes.  With millions of data points that have been meticulously extracted, organized, and standardized, the entire body of medical research literature is available at a remarkably granular level. The Company is now providing AI-enabled surveillance of both the published literature and adverse events as reported in regulatory databases. The company was founded in 2013 and headquartered in Broomfield, Colorado.
2018_description:
MedAware Systems’ Personalized Clinical Decision Support system provides healthcare professionals and their patients immediate and actionable information on medical treatments and outcomes. This new Scientific-Data-as-a-Service (SDaaS)™ solves the problem of making the vast and chaotic body of human clinical trials research instantly available and indispensable in developing the patient plan of care.

Historically, the most current information on effective, evidence-based treatments typically takes ten years, or more, to bubble up into standards of medical practice. The cost of this in terms of patient outcome and dollars wasted is staggering. The monumental study conducted by Dr. Don Berwick and his research team estimated that incorrect or ineffective medical treatments cost the US over $350 Billion per year. 

Theirs is a competitively priced subscription model initially targeted for millions of healthcare professionals, and later, directly to hundreds of millions of their patients, who are driving 160 million medical searches per day on Google. 

With the rapidly accelerating transition to Value-based healthcare in the US, there is now significant incentive for physicians and medical organizations to increase efficiency and improve patient outcome, coupled with financial penalties for not achieving better outcomes. 

Their new data service is positioned to become the de facto standard for informing physicians on the most effective treatment for each individual patient they see – quickly (in under 45 seconds) and accurately. Subscribers are able to filter this vast amount of data to provide first-ever individualized treatment efficacy information based on a unique patient profile, i.e., age, sex, race, severity of the condition, co-morbidities, etc.

2023_description: Baicells Technologies provides wireless broadband access solutions. Its technical solutions include Light4G which is a deployment solution for mobile operators to improve coverage and expand capacity in hotspot; BroFi WBB solution which is a multi-carrier intelligent broadband access system that triples the user capacity and provides 300 Mbps high-speed concurrent broadband; and WeLTE 4G wireless industry network solutions which provide multi-media services covering voice, cluster service, positioning, data collection, picture transmission, video call, high-definition monitoring ,and emergency communication for various industries. 2018_description:
 Vytalize Health is a tech-enabled, in home primary care provider for seniors combining telemedicine, house calls, and remote care coordination. Established in 2014, the founders of Vytalize Health came together based on a vision; efficient delivery of high quality healthcare without the administrative or brick and mortar waste of the current antiquated system at an unparalleled cost.  

By creating a solution that rethinks the inpatient setting, nurses deliver in home care while doctors diagnose and treat through technology, Vytalize Health began recruiting the best nurses, doctors and phlebotomists on its team and equipping them with the latest technology and medical equipment.  
 ---
2023_description:
 ---
 Vytalize Health is a new kind of Medicare ACO. Vytalize partners with primary care practices and power them through bold financial incentives and smart technology. By specializing in Medicare services, it provides an all-in-one solution that is efficient and effective. Vytalize collaborates with practice partners to help them deliver the best medical care to their Medicare patients, while simultaneously lowering the overall cost of care.  In 2018, Vytalize wrapped up a successful clinical care model with an enhanced business model that allowed us and our physician partners to share in the cost savings that were generated for Medicare. Today, its care delivery model transforms the healthcare experience for tens of thousands of Medicare beneficiaries across 14 states by helping them take control of their chronic conditions in collaboration with their doctors.  Vytalize's multidisciplinary clinical team serves as an extension of each physician to design custom-tailored care plans for each of their Medicare patients that are proven to prevent and reduce hospitalizations and improve quality of life.  As of 2022, the company has 500+ physicians throughout the US, 65K Medicare patients, and manages $2B in medical spending.

2023_description: Savvy Lane is a technology-enabled real estate brokerage representing represent people buying and selling homes.  Its mission is to use technology to empower consumers and agents to save time and money and increases productivity. The company's clients can choose between the company's platform or a local agent to buy or sell a home. Either option saves its customers half the commission per transaction. 2018_description:
Savvy Lane is a Technology-Powered Hybrid Real Estate Brokerage. We represent people buying and selling homes in 9 markets across 3 states. Our mission is to use technology to empower consumers and agents to save time, money and increase productivity.

Our strategy is simple. In a highly fragmented industry, we've brought together a team our technology experts and agents to create a faster, better service that costs less. Our focus is on efficiency and as a result, we don't carry the high operating costs that traditional models or competitors use. Our customers can choose to use our platform or a local agent to buy or sell a home. Either option saves our customer an average 2.5% per transaction, over the traditional 6% model.

2023_description: Welcome to Ellipsis Marketing. Our mission is to provide every small business a fair chance of success through well-organized marketing teams. If you are a small business, non-profit, or a startup, looking for new customers, and you are on a tight budget, our Readymade Marketing is the solution for you. In Readymade Marketing you simply pick the services and tasks you want to accomplish and leave the rest to us. Our well-organized network of local and global marketers works behind the scenes from custom designing your website, SEO program, or Ad Campaign, to managing them on an ongoing basis. There is no need to manage complex self-service marketing tools. There is full transparency around exactly what your marketing dollars are doing for you. And you don't have to go through the hassle of building and managing a local or remote marketing team yourself. Each of our Readymade Marketing Programs is designed to give you more time to focus on your business, save you money, and accurately measure return on investment from your marketing dollars. If our readymade marketing doesn’t cover what you are looking for, you can always hire us on a time-and-materials based engagement. In such cases you will be hiring us as an independent contractor and payment terms will depend on the complexity of the project.
2018_description:
Ellipsis Solutions helps Local Businesses find Customers in a Measurable, Affordable, and Easy Way. Campaigns are customized to fit a business type, location, budget and a specific need. They are designed to produce measurable results, save money and time. There are no setup fees or hidden fees of any sort. Businesses pay for the campaigns they run in simple monthly fixed payments.

Campaigns include Local Listings, SEO/SEM, Internet & Mobile Ads, Email Marketing, Social Media Marketing, Postcards, Letters, Flyers, Website, Blog, Print, Radio, TV, Appointment Reminders, Loyalty & Referral Programs, Online Review Management, Marketing Planning & Consulting.

Specially designed Local Marketing Campaigns that can be launched within seconds, called 5-mile Campaigns™, are available in select cities in the San Francisco Bay Area and for business types including Auto Repair, Bakeries, Bars, Lounges, Chiropractors, Cosmetics, Day Cares, Fitness Centers, Florists, Food Trucks, Furniture, Groceries, Home Furnishing Stores, Investment Advisors, Landscaping, Luxury Goods, Pet Sitting, Photography, Realtors, Appraisers, Restaurants, Salons, Travel Agencies, Merchandise, and Veterinarians.

Ellipsis is a proud member and supporter of Local Chambers of Commerce and offers generous discounts to fellow chamber members and non-profit organizations.

Let Ellipsis run your Local Marketing, so you can run your Local Business.

2023_description: The world has a bottomless appetite for electricity. In fact, 45% of the world's electricity passes through an electric motor. This is equivalent to 1 out of every 2 power plants solely dedicated to electric motors. And yet electric motor designs remain essentially unchanged in last 100 years.  Linear Labs, an electric motor company, has created an entirely new family of electric motor systems designed for the next generation of electric vehicles, HVAC systems and robotics welcoming in a new era of smarter energy utilization.   Our ''smart''​ motors shape shift and morph the physical design in real time to adjust for changing conditions. The result is 2x improvements in torque, further range and significantly lowering power consumption. Linear Labs is a Texas based technology company. www.linearlabsinc.com
2018_description:
Linear Labs Inc. ..

Their technologies  just  changed the electric motor/generator world forever ushering in a new era in how they think about electric machines...An entirely new technology utilizing different principles than all previous  electro-magnetic machines to date!. Incredibly  efficient, far more powerful, absolutely dead quiet, completely fault tolerant.Linear Labs Magnetic Tunnel Saturation designs offer extremely high flux confinement and flux densities allowing unparalleled conductor field saturation using conventional magnetic materials technologies.  Unlike all machines used today the smallest current is turned into a motive force. No current is consumed to establish a electro-magnetic field and there are no alternating magnetic poles thus best power factor available.. As near to unity power factor as it is possible to get!

So what does all that mean? Extremely high efficiency across the entire rpm/torque range, not just at one point on a graph. Electric vehicles that don't need new battery technology to get gasoline equivalence. Industrial motors that respond instantly to changing loads and continue to operate after a fault.

Linear Labs has produced technologies with the following attributes:

1.	Technology that is Proprietary and Patentable.  Patents pending on all technologies , 
         (Base technology claims awarded by PCT/EPO, entering country phase).

2.	Technology is Greenfield IP – Not like any other motor – differentiators are evident

3.	Technology that can replace existing technologies in existing and extremely large markets

4.	Technology focuses on a concentration of clearly defined major customers:  1 sale = large $

5.	Technology is a glove-fit for several large-cap global corporations, who are potential acquirers

6.	Technology that can be licensed, and utilize existing customer infrastructure to manufacture

7.	Technology that has been reduced to practice 4 times; 3rd party data confirms it works

Detailed Business Plan available on request

2023_description: Owkin is a French-American startup that uses artificial intelligence to find the right treatment for every patient. Our focus is to use AI to discover and develop better treatments for unmet medical needs, starting with the fight against cancer. They use AI to identify new drug candidates, de-risk and accelerate clinical trials and build diagnostic tools that improve patient outcomes.  Using federated learning, a pioneering collaborative AI framework, Owkin enables medical and biopharma partners to unlock valuable insights from siloed datasets, while protecting patient privacy and securing proprietary data.  Owkin was co-founded by Thomas Clozel MD, a clinical research doctor and former assistant professor in clinical onco-hematology, and Gilles Wainrib, a pioneer in the field of machine learning in biology, in 2016. Owkin has raised over $255 million and became a ‘unicorn’ – a startup valued at more than $1 billion – in November 2021 through a $180 million investment from French biopharma company Sanofi.
2018_description:
OWKIN is a predictive analytics company that utilizes transfer learning to accelerate drug discovery and development, with offices in Paris and New York City.

Our data scientists and machine learning engineers are among the best in the world, with publications in ICML, NIPS and other top scientific journals, and the team includes several Kaggle Masters (top 100 worldwide) and a DREAM Challenge top performer.

Our proprietary platform, OWKIN Socrates, uses machine learning-based modeling to analyze molecular, imaging libraries and patient datasets to uncover complex biomarker patterns that cause disease. We partner with leading pharmaceutical companies including Amgen and Actelion and we have programs in development with Institut Curie, Centre Leon Berard and Saint Louis Hospital.

We aim to improve drug discovery and development using collective intelligence built on real-world patient data. We transform hospitals full of unstructured datasets into thousands of accurate diagnostic and predictive models, augmenting and accelerating physicians’ capabilities. This real-world collective intelligence and access to data is transferable to the pharmaceutical industry and can empower predictive analytics, biomarker discovery and post-market analysis.

2018_description:
KPI Therapeutics (KPI)™ is a new collaborative initiative between drug development firms and private investors.

KPI has a vision for a better way to develop early- and mid-stage therapies to meet the many unmet needs of patients. The basic ingredients may seem obvious: potentially groundbreaking therapeutic candidates that could truly change the lives of patients; diversified and highly experienced commercial drug developers; and the necessary resources to move the programs forward. But it is not that simple to take the ingredients and come up with major new therapies. Companies need vision, creativity, and exciting new development approaches that can benefit and inspire all of the participants in the process to be prosperous and successful.

KPI was built from the ground up to be that type of inspiring and prosperous drug development company. It is a new collaborative initiative between drug development firms and private investors. It was founded on the belief that while there has been an explosion of new science and medical research, there has not been a concurrent increase in the development of novel drugs. With aging populations and many neglected diseases on the increase, the need for new approaches to bringing more effective medicines to people has never been greater. At KPI, we believe that as an industry we can do better than develop just 20 to 30 new drugs per year. Our vision of KPI is to speed the progression of promising drug candidates through the critical translational stage of development and work with commercialization partners who have a strong commitment to improving access to important new medicines.

2023_description: As one of the fastest growing startups in Los Angeles, we're revolutionizing the way in which companies approach successful video advertising. Our team of award-winning Producers, Editors, Directors, Engineers, and Performance Marketing Managers are building a global studio where we can conceptualize, shoot, and produce hundreds of videos per day. Unlike traditional advertising agencies that pitch creative concepts for companies, hope they will perform, and outsource filming, we design videos that are guaranteed to convert. We use data to guide our creative process and leverage testing and analysis to make adjustments to react to users in real-time. What's atypical about the company: 1. We're fast and data-driven: our teams develop concepts in the morning, shoot/edit in the afternoon, launch in the evening, and iterate the next day based on real-world performance. 2. We’re a behavioral R&D lab at the core: We put 2,000+ video experiments per week, watched by tens of millions of people per day, that give us deep insights into how people make decisions. Over the past couple of years, we’ve built an enormous library of IP around human behavior and visual communication. 3. We work on a pure pay for performance basis. Zero production fees for video. Clients only pay us if our videos outperform anything they’re running internally.
2018_description:
TubeScience produces conversion-optimized video for many of Facebook’s largest performance marketers. Three factors set the company apart from competitors: 

1) TubeScience places a huge premium on speed and data-driven creative decisions. Its in-house teams will develop a concept in the morning, shoot/edit in the afternoon, launch multivariate video experiments in the evening, and iterate the next day based on real-world performance data. So in the weeks or months it takes a traditional creative agency to produce a single video, TubeScience will be on version 15 baking in weeks of insights.

2) All efforts are focused on scalable—rather than one-off—wins. For many clients TubeScience produces 100+ videos per week to support multi-million dollar monthly FB budgets. 

3) The company operates on a pure pay-for-performance basis, with zero production fees for video. That allows TubeScience to focus 100% of its efforts on providing measurable value to partners.

2023_description: Swag’r is the leading augmented reality SDK for instant brand activation at live events. The Swag’r content delivery platform uses A/R, gamification, and targeted geolocation technologies to drive unprecedented fan engagement with national, regional, and local brands by delivering any manner of branded content in gamified ways across live event maps. Swag’r consistently outperforms legacy advertising channels while adding a whole new layer of fun and value to fans. Additionally, the platform can delivery any manner of content, redefining the cutting-edge digital real estate market. Swag’r is the bridge between where you want to be and where your customers or clients already are.
2018_description: SWAG'R is the Pokemon Go for brands!  Swag’r is a whole new way for brands to engage with mobile consumers.  We use gamification and location based technologies so brands can communicate with users when they are in predicable locations like a college campus, shopping mall, sporting event, or a military base.  When people gather in predicable locations they become predicable in their consumer, social media and mobile habits.  We use this data to engage relative brand content at these predicable locations with very simple to very complex digital gamification activities. Swag’r geo fences a specific location and places brand content in the form of a pin point in strategic locations on the swag’r map.  When a swag’r user gets close to a pin point swag‘r will sent the user a push notification asking them if they would like some swag, explaining what the brand content is.  Since the content is relative to the demographic group the results of the engagement is as much as 10X then traditional mobile engagement.  Swag’r also has developed the 1st first ever human/digital scavenger hunt technology for brands.  Swag’r can place digital tokens inside of the geo-fenced area and the swag’r users must collect digital tokens physically and if they grab all the required digital token specified in the conditions of the hunt then a reward will populate in the users swagbag from one of our brand partners.  This platform swag’r has built will forever change the way brands communicate with mobile consumers.

2023_description: Mighty plays streaming music on-the-go without a phone, screen, or Internet connection. It's the perfect way to break free from your phone during runs, trips to the gym, and commutes, and to entertain your kids without more screen time. Mighty launched in July 2017 with a Spotify partnership and new streaming partners will be introduced in the coming months. Mighty has 50,000 users in 65 countries. Mighty Audio offers a mobile app for iOS and Android that is used to wirelessly sync Spotify Music to the Mighty via the player’s Bluetooth and Wi-Fi. Once the app is installed on your phone, the rest of the setup process takes about 10 minutes. That includes creating a Mighty account, renaming your device something only you will understand, connecting it to WiFi, downloading updates and linking your Spotify account. Once all of that is done, all you have to do is select which playlists to sync from Spotify to Mighty. Once the music is stored on Mighty, the user no longer needs a phone or Internet connection for music playback. Mighty has a 3.5mm headset jack and also works with Bluetooth headphones. Mighty makes Spotify mobile without using any of your phone's storage, battery or data.

OmniBazaar is a community-owned, rewards-driven, cryptocurrency-enabled, peer-to-peer, e-commerce marketplace. The OmniBazaar system includes its own built-in cryptocurrency (OmniCoin), an influencer marketing system, social messaging, reputation tracking, escrow agents, and bonuses to provide user incentives for participation and growth. With OmniBazaar, online sellers save 90% of the fees they currently pay Amazon or eBay. Online buyers benefit from lower prices, and escape from "big data" tracking and "push" marketing. Social influencers enjoy a simple way to monetize their social networks. Marketplace buyers and sellers can generate additional income by providing services in the marketplace. 

OmniBazaar software is currently in private beta testing. We invite beta testers at http://beta.omnibazaar.com, and we are open to investor inquiries.

2023_description: QuantumStreet AI automates the design, testing, and ongoing analysis of investment strategies using artificial intelligence. The world's largest financial institutions have built award winning strategies that have led to billions of dollars around the world. Investment professionals can now easily access AI to analyze more data and create innovative solutions. 2018_description:
EquBot was born during a Haas MBA classroom discussion at UC Berkeley. EquBot is a technology company that is disrupting the investment process. Our powerful artificial intelligence provides investors unique investment insights. EquBot is an IBM Global Entrepreneur Company and powered by IBM Watson. EquBot's technology is powering the first AI based ETF and Robo Analysis platform.  

Technology:
The EquBot technology is intelligently powered by IBM Watson and EquBot’s proprietary algorithms. The technology is a multi staged process that seeks to identify mispriced stocks in the marketplace and then exploits the timing of those mispriced stocks. First, the technology uses massive amounts of data to build predictive financial models on over 6,000 publicly traded US companies to identify those whose values are not fully recognized by the market. Next, the technology parses million of articles and news sources to uncover catalysts and events to quantify the probability of realizing those opportunities. Such analysis, with the power of IBM Watson, determines strategic entry and exit points.

2023_description: Are you familiar with the situation when your favorite product is not on the shelf, because it’s in “out of stock”? Or when you need to wait in long checkout lines?  Techshelf technology reduces shelf “out of stocks” and creates an automated checkout process for shoppers. With over 10 years of experience in distribution and retail, we created a cost efficient solution that will change physical retail forever.
2018_description:
I am almost sure that everyone of us faced the situation when you cannot find your favorite product on the shelf while shopping, because the product is in “out of stock”. Probably it’s not the biggest problem in our lives, but it’s a big problem for the companies. Every year companies from retail industry are losing more than 600 bln. $, because of some simple out of stocks on the shelves. 

Tech Shelf has a solution for that. We provide real time data from the shelves directly to retailers, producers and distributors. Techshelf inform our clients’ employees before the out of stock happens, shelves are replenished more efficient and in that way we boost our customers sales. 

We use modules and censors to collect data and literally we can equip any existing shelf in store and start to offer real-time data now.  

More than this, after having big amount of data collected and analyzed using our specially designed software and algorithms - TechShelf is able to   
•Make a real-time inventory management.
•Understand sales performance of every product at each point of contact within the same store.
•Increase customer loyalty.
•Optimize Employee Productivity.
•Give access to real time data from the shelves and help our customers employees take informed decisions and be more effective that they ever been.

Our team has over 10 years of combined experience in distribution, merchandising, and retail. We needed these solutions previously for ourselves and after we developed the product for our own needs, we realized it’s potential for the entire industry.  

Currently there are different solutions on the market, but the reason they are still not on the real supermarket shelves is that the price of existing solutions, are much higher, than losses due to the out of stocks and misplaced items. We offer practical, affordable and flexible solutions. Our smart panels with modules and censors are created to be easily installed by anyone on the shelves. 

Nowadays everything becomes smart and we believe that retail must be smart as well! Our team is ready to make it happen, in order to help people, find the right product, at the right place at anytime!

2023_description: Positron offers the first chair that is designed specifically for fully immersive cinematic VR. It invented the world's first full-motion VR chair which is the Voyager and has partnered with the likes of Universal Studios, Disney, Walmart, Verizon, and many more to bring VR films to audiences in museums, theaters, and malls across the world.  The beauty of its VR platform is it provides a completely immersive experience but with 50% less footprint than competitor platforms, eliminates motion sickness, and offers the very best exclusive VR content from the best creative studios in the world. It was founded in 2014 and is headquartered in Montrose, California.
2018_description:
ENGINEERING MAGIC.

Creators of Voyager, the world's first full motion platform for cinematic VR.  

Positron Studios, an affiliated company, also provides customized virtual reality experiences, immersive multi-sensory installations,  motion simulators,  interactive marketing and sales tools.

________________


VOYAGER

Designed and created by filmmakers and engineers at Positron, Voyager™ is a full-motion platform for premium cinematic VR experiences. The chair provides a highly comfortable, fully integrated personal experience that incorporates robotic rotation and reclining, haptic feedback, spatial audio, scent technology, and specialized seating for motion-synchronized theaters.  

With its smooth mechanical motion, comfortable seat design, and surreally silent motors, Positron's Voyager™ is the first ever immersive cinematic VR platform designed for communal theater settings.  It creates a feeling that you must experience for yourself to understand.

We're happy to announce that less than 0.2% of users report motion sickness in Voyager™, compared to 20% of people who report motion sickness in VR in general. In fact, many people who previously were susceptible to motion sickness in VR and avoided donning a headset, now enthusiastically report they can watch VR on this platform.

Voyager has already been embraced as the cinematic VR platform of choice by companies such as Universal Studios, IMAX, Intel, Legend VR, and received accolades from top VR filmmakers such as Chris Milk, Ted Schilowitz, Nonny De La Peña, A.R. Rahman, Eliza McNitt, Baobab Studios, Milica Zec & Winslow Porter, and Sundance 2017 VR filmmakers who showcased their work this year on Voyager™.  

A limited amount of premium Voyager™ units are currently available to lease for premieres, film festivals, and VIP events.  Pre-orders are being taken for our first major production batch for upcoming installations at theaters, hotels, airport lounges, and VR screening rooms . Stay tuned for announcements on the first rollout of Voyager™ technology available in locations for the general public.  Contact us to learn more.

2023_description: MACH37 is the premier accelerator for entrepreneurs and startups that are solving important problems in the fields of cybersecurity, autonomous vehicles, artificial intelligence, cyber-physical systems, IoT, industrial controls, or other cyber-related fields where security is critically important. We go beyond the traditional model of typical startup accelerators by bringing our innovators focused mentorship and support from our exclusive Stars Mentor Network that is comprised of visionaries, practitioners, and successful entrepreneurs from across the cyber industry. Twice a year, MACH37 invests in a cohort of 5-10 cyber startups, each of which participates in an intensive 3-month program that emphasizes coaching, mentorship, and validation of their solution for product/market fit. Throughout the program, startups are introduced to investors and key public and private sector organizations in the Washington DC metro area. Our program is designed to propel cyber startups into the marketplace, equipped with the skills to connect with customers, grow and compete for funding, and generate traction. The program culminates with a Demo Day presentation to 150-200 investors.  MACH37 was established in 2013 as a division of the Virginia-based Center for Innovative Technology (CIT) with funding from the Commonwealth of Virginia. In 2017 CIT partnered with VentureScope, a strategic innovation consultancy and venture investment firm, to revamp MACH37's operating model and curriculum. In 2018, VentureScope acquired majority ownership of MACH37. Following a successful partnership between CIT and VentureScope, MACH37 became fully owned and operated by VentureScope in 2020. MACH37 focuses primarily on honing and strengthening startups' product-market fit through extensive customer discovery and market research, expanding emerging companies' professional networks, fostering founder wellbeing, and providing emerging companies in the cyber security industry with access to investment capital and an immediate customer base. In an October 2020 article, Forbes named MACH37 'the Granddaddy' of top cyber accelerators giving a nod to the fact that MACH37 was one of the first accelerators in the world dedicated to cyber and cyber adjacent technologies and has lasted far longer than many of its peer accelerators while strengthening over time.  The name 'MACH37' is a reference to the escape velocity of Earth's atmosphere and the accelerator's goal to help cyber startups GET LAUNCHED. VentureScope receives 5% equity from each MACH37 startup. 2023_description:
 ---
 MACH37 is the premier accelerator for entrepreneurs and startups that are solving important problems in the fields of cybersecurity, autonomous vehicles, artificial intelligence, cyber-physical systems, IoT, industrial controls, or other cyber-related fields where security is critically important. We go beyond the traditional model of typical startup accelerators by bringing our innovators focused mentorship and support from our exclusive Stars Mentor Network that is comprised of visionaries, practitioners, and successful entrepreneurs from across the cyber industry. Twice a year, MACH37 invests in a cohort of 5-10 cyber startups, each of which participates in an intensive 3-month program that emphasizes coaching, mentorship, and validation of their solution for product/market fit. Throughout the program, startups are introduced to investors and key public and private sector organizations in the Washington DC metro area. Our program is designed to propel cyber startups into the marketplace, equipped with the skills to connect with customers, grow and compete for funding, and generate traction. The program culminates with a Demo Day presentation to 150-200 investors.  MACH37 was established in 2013 as a division of the Virginia-based Center for Innovative Technology (CIT) with funding from the Commonwealth of Virginia. In 2017 CIT partnered with VentureScope, a strategic innovation consultancy and venture investment firm, to revamp MACH37's operating model and curriculum. In 2018, VentureScope acquired majority ownership of MACH37. Following a successful partnership between CIT and VentureScope, MACH37 became fully owned and operated by VentureScope in 2020. MACH37 focuses primarily on honing and strengthening startups' product-market fit through extensive customer discovery and market research, expanding emerging companies' professional networks, fostering founder wellbeing, and providing emerging companies in the cyber security industry with access to investment capital and an immediate customer base. In an October 2020 article, Forbes named MACH37 'the Granddaddy' of top cyber accelerators giving a nod to the fact that MACH37 was one of the first accelerators in the world dedicated to cyber and cyber adjacent technologies and has lasted far longer than many of its peer accelerators while strengthening over time.  The name 'MACH37' is a reference to the escape velocity of Earth's atmosphere and the accelerator's goal to help cyber startups GET LAUNCHED. VentureScope receives 5% equity from each MACH37 startup. Qualifying MACH37 startups are also eligible for an equity investment.

For the Brand, Makeena provides a streamlined, location-aware mobile and web customer engagement platform for natural and sustainable brands, automating tracking and redemption for the shopper across multiple platforms, brands, and retailers at the point of purchase (on-line or in-store) for a single shopper account. By pushing location and context aware incentives to shoppers, then tracking and rewarding their engagement, brands build new customers, and increase loyalty and repeat purchases. On the backend, brands upload their own information and decide where, when, and how much to offer. Makeena then collects the shopper data and provides the brands with a way to analyze and manage that data, delivering to the brands deeper shopper insights, where their products are located (in what stores and where on the shelf), and what encourages their shoppers to stay loyal to them.

2023_description: WHO WE ARE 24 Proof based out of the Silicon Slopes in Utah. We built a patent-pending technology to allow for proof of concept prototyping via a networked hackathon that we are extending into more offerings. WHAT WE DO We Hack it  We curate coders by invitation only, and then we match them to projects and clients after they have proven their skills to us.  Our hack it platform allows clients to hire directly or assign project work to coders.  We Build it   Clients come to us with a need which we then assign a lead developer to address. This need quickly turns into a development plan with estimate and timeline.  When client agrees, we build a team using our curated coders and work begins. We Prove it  We will test or pre-screen applicants for you all major programming languages for them to prove their knowledge not just answer simple CS based questions, real programming you pick from a growing library to cover actual work on the job, not silly questions. We Run it  Our proprietary software runs online hackathon, allows for coders to push code, clients can demo and choose the winner. We track user volume via a custom point system that as coders place and clients have successful projects, they both earn additional benefits. We Staff it  Our platform is built to support introducing positive experiences and allows for placement in addition to our Hack it, Build it.
2018_description:
24 Proof based out of Silicon Slopes in Utah, but we are opening region US locations with international dreams shortly yet we are open to remote developers as long as the code is yours and can pass code reviews we are happy. Our mission is to advance the rapid development of new technology and new brands drawing from a deeper talent pool of coders, in a competitive, code first environment.

24 Proof matches experienced coders with clients via an invite-only 24-hour coding competitions. At the end of the contest, the client has an MVP, and the top 3 developers walk away with payment for their time and skill. Coders need to qualify for each skill before it gets listed on their profile which will only enable them to be invited to a competition once confirmed through a series of coding tasks.

For those clients that need custom solutions, we introduced them to our agency, where talented coders, designers, project managers and QA professionals work part-time hours in their spare time, so clients get the talent without the high budget.

2023_description: Synova's waste-to-chemicals technology is a superior form of chemical recycling designed to displace the need for virgin fuels and reduce climate impacts. Synova is focused on enhancing the circular economy of plastics and helping consumer product and petrochemical companies achieve targets for reducing waste and utilizing more recycled plastics. Synova's patented technology is uniquely poised to close the current gap in the plastic value chain. Able to process MSW, including mixed plastic waste, the technology also features a 'best in class' cleanup train that removes 99.5% of unwanted tars and uses the energy value to create a highly efficient process with a better CO2 footprint. The result is a gas made up of high value molecules that have numerous applications, including BTX and olefins (the building blocks for new plastics), RNG and electricity. Synova's technology has more than 8,000 hours of independently-verified testing.
2018_description: Synova is an international developer of waste-to-energy projects. The company's unique proposition uses a proprietary technology to gasify and strip unrecycled waste of its contaminants, creating a stable, green alternative to natural gas, suitable for chemical production or use in combined cycle gas turbines, the most efficient form of power production. The net effect hereof reduces greenhouse gas, forever precludes collected waste from entering our fresh water or oceans, and substantially reduces the need to boost tipping fees.

2023_description: Otter.ai offers a collaborative note-taking app that makes important information from voice conversations including meetings, interviews, and lectures instantly accessible and actionable. We are proud to be supported by some of Silicon Valley’s top venture capitalists who were early investors in Tesla, SpaceX, Slack, and Twitter. 2023_description: We’re a next generation private investment firm with a unique model for our investors to access the private markets. In addition to making principal investments in venture to growth stage companies, we offer our family office, institutional, and strategic investors access to vetted direct and co-investment opportunities primarily in FinTech / InsurTech / PropTech. Our mandate includes any technology or service that could be synergistic to a bank, insurance or financial service company. RueOne supplements the traditional fund structure by allowing our investors to participate in individual venture capital and private equity transactions with the benefit of our sourcing, structuring, due diligence, domain expertise, and professional management. We operate exclusively as an investment advisor, not a broker dealer, and we are compensated exclusively by our investors. Our participation in a potential investment opportunity comes in the form of a principal investment by RueOne as a general partner and/or direct & co-investments from our family office and institutional clients.  STAGE We make investments ranging from early stage venture capital to growth stage private equity. We do not look to take technology or product risk around proof of concept. However, we are well-positioned to help management teams with go-to-market strategies, scaling their business, and executing their vision. We like to invest in companies where our capital can be used to fuel revenue growth, drive efficiencies, and/or make strategic acquisitions. FINANCIALS While we are flexible around our revenue and EBITDA requirements, we generally do not make investments in pre-revenue companies. SECTORS We are opportunistic and have historically invested across sectors. 2023_description: Kidmoto is a unique service catering to traveling parents with small children. The Kidmoto App provides a solution to a real problem with family airport car travel. Taxi’s and car services do not provide securely harnessed and installed car seats for children and therefore parents fear traveling with their small children. The Kidmoto app connects parents to a network of professionally trained drivers who provide secured child car seats for safe airport and cruise car transportation.
2018_description:
Kidmoto Technologies™ started in New York City in November 2016 with the vision of providing safe airport taxi transportation for families with small children. Kidmoto aims to help safety-minded parents navigate the complex and hazardous world of airport transportation.

Kidmoto created a solution to a real problem and provides a fresh perspective on the day-to-day hardships that parents face. Car services and taxis do not provide installed car seats. Too often, parents are faced with the reality of just “jumping into a cab” with unrestrained children.
 
The Kidmoto mission is to provide the convenience of accessible and safe airport taxi transportation for families by growing a network of drivers that provide professionally secured car seats for safe airport transportation.
 
The Kidmoto app connects parents to a network of professionally-trained, Kidmoto certified, drivers. The concept of providing safe family airport transportation is now a reality, due to the efforts of CEO Nelson Nigel, a lifelong entrepreneur and former NYC yellow taxi driver. 
 
Currently Kidmoto Technologies™ addresses the safe transportation safety needs of parents traveling to or from NYC airports and plans for national growth.  
 
Kidmoto also provides Kidrent, which is an add-on service, providing parents the convenience of renting strollers and Pack N Play play areas while staying in NYC.

2023_description: We are working to increase diversity, inclusion, and impact in early-stage investing and our entrepreneurial ecosystem through our innovative learning-by-doing progressive fund model. Our global fund has 99 women investors, 25 of them women of color, which is led by an experienced investment committee of ten women. We are building a portfolio of investments in early-stage impact companies, diversified across industry and geography, over a four year investment period. We will make 6-8 investments in each of the first two years and then do some selected follow-on investments in those companies in years three and four. We are excited about this model, building on two pilots in the United States and Europe (the Rising Tide Pilots) with nearly 200 women, which made 18 investments. Together, we are creating the next wave of educated and trained angel investors focused on both social impact and financial returns, which are investing in underrepresented entrepreneurs.
2018_description:
The goal of Next Wave Ventures is to drive diversity in high growth entrepreneurship and angel investing by increasing the participation of underrepresented groups.

The first initiatives of Next Wave Ventures are the Rising Tide US Fund I, which is co-managed with Portfolia, and the Rising Tide Europe Fund I, managed by Go Beyond Investing. These learning by doing funds seek to narrow the gender gap in angel investing by providing women the education and training they need to become sophisticated angel investors, while offering them a unique learning opportunity that allows them to build a diversified portfolio of investments, receive mentoring by women who are experienced angel investors, as well a diversified online education & training program and opportunities for local, regional, and national events, including a women’s investor summit in San Diego in October 2016, which is sponsored by the Kauffman Foundation.

Future programs will focus on minority investors, social impact investing, investing in emerging markets, and investments that disrupt animal agriculture.

2023_description: Privakey’s mission is to simplify how people confirm their identities, assert their intent and respond to any challenge.  We improve the customer experience and security of digital interactions by eliminating the reliance on passwords, “security” questions and other forms of identity confirmation that introduce known security vulnerabilities and frustrate users. Our embedded software solution transforms existing mobile apps into strong customer authorizers, streamlining many existing workflows.   Services use Privakey to send users challenges—a new form of secure engagement within apps. Challenges include traditional identity assertions, confirmations of intent and any type of message that may require a response.  Challenges can be as simple as a Yes/No response from a user, to as rich as digitally approving actionable contract terms. Privakey works by turning users’ mobile phones into cryptographically-based, secure customer identifiers.  Customers using Privakey-enabled apps simply respond to challenges delivered to their phones with a message body that can contain any type of interactive digital content such as HTML, PDFs and forms.  Once the user has responded to a challenge, it is digitally signed and returned to the sender. To ensure a frictionless, but secure user experience, challenges can be configured to require a user to assert a biometric or PIN as a second factor of assurance.
2018_description:
Privakey is an innovative and revolutionary approach to digital identity. Our cloud-based authentication service offer a single, consistent, and secure method that users can use to access websites, apps, and online services.

Privakey is a cloud based identity service that eliminates passwords and enables multifactor authentication, with the ease of a social login.  Privakey’s service is similar to an ATM transaction, where consumers use the same PIN and have the same experience for every login transaction.  

Our solution eliminates the frustration that users feel with managing multiple account logins while at the same time reducing the business risk of password breaches by deploying multi-factor authentication.

 Privakey is an innovative and revolutionary approach to digital identity. Our cloud-based authentication service offer a single, consistent, and secure method that users can use to access websites, apps, and online services.

Privakey is a cloud based identity service that eliminates passwords and enables multifactor authentication, with the ease of a social login.  Privakey’s service is similar to an ATM transaction, where consumers use the same PIN and have the same experience for every login transaction.  

Our solution eliminates the frustration that users feel with managing multiple account logins while at the same time reducing the business risk of password breaches by deploying multi-factor authentication.
 ---
2023_description:
 ---
 Privakey’s mission is to simplify how people confirm their identities, assert their intent and respond to any challenge.  We improve the customer experience and security of digital interactions by eliminating the reliance on passwords, “security” questions and other forms of identity confirmation that introduce known security vulnerabilities and frustrate users. Our embedded software solution transforms existing mobile apps into strong customer authorizers, streamlining many existing workflows.   Services use Privakey to send users challenges—a new form of secure engagement within apps. Challenges include traditional identity assertions, confirmations of intent and any type of message that may require a response.  Challenges can be as simple as a Yes/No response from a user, to as rich as digitally approving actionable contract terms. Privakey works by turning users’ mobile phones into cryptographically-based, secure customer identifiers.  Customers using Privakey-enabled apps simply respond to challenges delivered to their phones with a message body that can contain any type of interactive digital content such as HTML, PDFs and forms.  Once the user has responded to a challenge, it is digitally signed and returned to the sender. To ensure a frictionless, but secure user experience, challenges can be configured to require a user to assert a biometric or PIN as a second factor of assurance.

FaceTec's patented, industry-leading Certified 3D Liveness Detection, face matching, optical character recognition, and age estimation technology biometrically binds the unique, live, 3D user to their account, anchoring a secure chain of trust for mobile and web applications. 2023_description: Philometrics is a group composed of social scientists and computer engineers, aiming to transform survey research. It founders began as academics at the University of Cambridge, working on finding scalable ways to understand how people think. It was founded to help bring technology to the masses, in which researchers would be empowered to do the most cutting edge work they can--and without adding big barriers to entry. Its SurveyExtender method produces insight on a revolutionary scale, empowering clients to understand people, markets, and competitors more deeply and accurately than ever before. Philometrics' team is formed of experienced business analysts and leading academic researchers, all of whom are experienced in helping academics and companies utilize the power of detailed survey insight.
2018_description:
We are a group of social scientists and computer engineers who are passionate about transforming survey research. Our founders began as academics at the University of Cambridge, working on finding scalable ways to understand how people think. The survey--a 120 year old instrument of choice for most social scientists--became the focus of this work. We found that a combination of big data, machine learning, and survey acumen could lead to remarkable results: Hundreds of thousands of responses to virtually any survey - and at a fraction of the typical cost.

Philometrics was founded to help bring our technology to the masses. We are passionate about empowering researchers to do the most cutting edge work they can--and without adding big barriers to entry. Philometrics was built on these ideas. We wanted to be powerful, innovative, fast, and easy to use. We wanted to optimize research through the power of online behavioural big data analysis - from a study of 1000 respondents we aim to give you the insight of 100,000+ people!

2023_description: Companion Health Technologies is a remote patient monitoring system that dramatically improves the quality of life for seniors. They offer a suite of solutions developed by Information technology specialists and doctorate level research scientists to help clients achieve greater efficiency in data gathering, outcomes measurement, and clinical treatment solutions. 2023_description: Rowing Blazers is a New York-based brand known for its colorful, sporty, slightly subversive take on the classics, as well as its cult following and limited-edition collaborations.  Founded by American designer Jack Carlson in 2017, the brand combines elements from the worlds of tailoring, sportswear, and streetwear — helping to redefine “preppy” and bringing the classics to new audiences and a new generation. Rowing Blazers began as a tailoring house dedicated to crafting club blazers (the world’s first sporting uniforms).  Today the brand continues this tradition, but also draws inspiration from the the “preppy” canon and the world of sport more broadly.  Beyond tailoring, Rowing Blazers is also known for its rugby and polo shirts, outerwear, knits, leisurewear, accessories, and fast-selling collaborations with the likes of Umbro, FILA, Seiko, Noah, Eric Emanuel, Barbour, and more. Named one of the top ten fastest-growing DTC brands in the world in 2021, Rowing Blazers has developed a cult following that includes Timothée Chalamet, Gwyneth Paltrow, Dwyane Wade, Emily Ratajkowski, Justin and Hailey Bieber, Mindy Kaling, Chloë Sevigny, Russell Westbrook, BTS, Tan France, B.J. Novak, Carmelo Anthony, Ashley Graham, Lukas Gage, Maude Apatow, Randall Park, Wayne Diamond, Millie Bobby Brown, Ziwe Fumudoh, Jordan Clarkson, Will Ferrell, Tom Daly, Finn Wolfhard, Gaten Matarazzo, Joe Keery, Charles Melton, Christian Pulisic, Donovan Mitchell, Whitney Peak, Tom Daley, Madelaine Petsch, Ronny Chieng, Romeo Beckham, Tracy Morgan, Dax Shepard, Mario Carbone, Thundercat, A$AP Nast, Macklemore, and Pete Davidson. Rowing Blazers works with some of the best fabric mills, artisans, and workshops in the world, all of whom share the brand’s own dedication to quality, traditional craftsmanship, and ethical sourcing.  Community has always been an important part of Rowing Blazers’ brand — with packed events at its New York flagship and partnerships with a wide range of organizations including Row New York, Play Rugby USA, Save the Children, the NAACP, and more.

Rowing Blazers is an irreverent, cryptic, Made-in-NYC apparel brand, inspired by the eponymous book by US national team rower and archaeologist Jack Carlson.

Rowing Blazers is principally a direct-to-consumer e-commerce brand, but is also available at some of the world's most influential menswear retailers, including United Arrows and BEAMS in Japan.

2023_description: Code Fellows is the Pacific Northwest’s premier technical skills training academy, delivering high-quality live instruction both online and in person to people from all backgrounds. Learners are guided toward vocational change and life transformation through software development, technical operations, cybersecurity and career training. They guide people from all backgrounds to change their lives through fast-paced, career-focused education. They shape passionate learners with immersive training to meet industry needs and improve diversity. Code Fellows has taught over 1,600 graduates and iterated on their curriculum and format to ensure students receive the most industry-relevant training as effectively and efficiently as possible. Students are immersed in their learning with daily lectures, pair programming, weekly presentations from full-time instructional staff who are seasoned industry professionals, one-week project sprints, and more. Code Fellows graduates work at Amazon, Microsoft, Zillow, Expedia, XBOX, NIKE, Starbucks, Nordstrom, and over 800 other companies. The modular style of the Code Fellows program allows students to test into the course level that is most appropriate for their current skill level. In addition, the modular class structure allows students to choose the schedule and timing that meets their needs. Code Fellows believes everyone should have the opportunity to succeed. In reality, many qualified candidates aren’t pursuing careers in a technology-related field because they are discouraged somewhere along the way. That’s why Code Fellows offers scholarships to help individuals who come from underserved and underrepresented backgrounds find rewarding careers in tech.  They are committed to breaking down systemic barriers and ensuring all people are treated with respect and dignity. They are united with their staff, students, alumni, and partners in the fight against systemic racism and injustice. Code Fellows supports both domestic and international licensing partners through its Powered by Code Fellows program.  Through this program they form strategic partnerships in markets all around the globe to help individuals transform their lives through education. Along with vocation-specific, continuously evolving curriculum and teaching materials, they invest in the success of their partners by providing marketing material, training for instructors, guidance and support on promoting, launching, and running courses, and more. Code Fellows partners are respected organizations in their industry who want to bring tech training to more individuals. Some of them include Oregon Department of Education, Apprenti, CSNP, Luminus Technical University College, and Cayman Enterprise City. Code Fellows also offers a tutoring program and platform to both students and non-students, technical instructor certification, and corporate training.

Students that are accepted into Code Fellows 8 week bootcamp receive instruction from successful industry practitioners in an immersive one-on-one environment. Courses are available in Ruby on Rails, Javascript, Python, and iOS. 

Code Fellows also offers on-location employee training bootcamps for companies that want to keep their employees up to date with the latest techniques and best practices.

2023_description: RAPT Therapeutics is a clinical stage immunology-based biopharmaceutical company focused on discovering, developing and commercializing oral small molecule therapies for patients with significant unmet needs in oncology and inflammatory diseases. Utilizing its proprietary discovery and development engine, the company is developing highly selective small molecules designed to modulate the critical immune responses underlying these diseases. In its first four years since inception, RAPT has discovered and advanced two unique drug candidates, each targeting C-C motif chemokine receptor 4. The company’s lead oncology drug candidate, FLX475, reached the clinic in just two and a half years with its lead inflammation drug candidate, RPT193, also in the clinic. The company is also pursuing a range of targets, including general control nonderepressible 2 and hematopoietic progenitor kinase 1, that are in the discovery stage of development.
2018_description: FLX Bio, Inc. is an immuno-oncology company focused on the discovery and development of orally-available, small molecule drugs to activate the immune system and eradicate cancer. Using its integrated immuno-oncology drug discovery platform, FLX Bio’s small molecule compounds specifically target proteins and pathways important for regulatory T cells or myeloid cells within the tumor microenvironment. Its lead candidate, a best-in-class CCR4 inhibitor, entered Phase 1 studies in December 2017 and has the potential to be used alone or in combination with checkpoint inhibitors to treat a variety of cancers. The company employs a precision medicine strategy for prospective patient selection in clinical studies, applying its robust computational and translational biology capabilities to identify key biomarkers that should maximize clinical response and increase the probability of clinical success.

2023_description: WeeAct is the free, decision-making iOS app where users make smarter decisions by crowd-voting choices with others and then sharing the outcomes. How It Works: CREATE – Post an everyday decision and two choices. VOTE - Other users vote on which choice you should pick. DECIDE - Review the votes, make your decision, and share the outcome of your decision with everyone who voted. Launch a WeeAct campaign around any decision using text and pictures. Here are some example decisions that WeeAct can help you make: - Fashion: What outfit should I wear? - Lifestyle: Which haircut should I get? - Consumer: What brand should I buy? - Blogging: Which tutorial should I post next on my blog? - Events: Which party should I go to tonight? - Design: What color should I paint my room? - Investing: Which stock should I buy? - Romance: Who should I go out on a date with? - Education: Which class should I enroll in? - Fitness: What should I do for my workout? - Health: What food should I eat on my diet? - Social: Which picture should I use in my profile? WeeAct Benefits: ● Create a decision campaign and harness the wisdom of the crowd in just seconds. ● Don't passively browse content. Participate in the decision-making of other users by voting on their choices and inspiring them to act. ● Stop scrolling through feeds of content that you don't care about. Automatically personalize your feed on WeeAct because every time you vote on a decision, you'll receive relevant content that shows the outcome. ● Stop wasting time looking at ads. WeeAct does not support or show ads anywhere on the app and all of our content is crowd-sourced by regular, everyday people, just like you! ● Think you give good advice? See for yourself using WeeAct's Voting Accuracy which tracks how often what you picked is the choice that gets made. ● Get feedback without the noise. Harassment is a major issue on some apps, but on WeeAct users cannot message each other and no one can post comments on campaigns. ● Create content your audience wants. Make your audience feel like they are part of the creative decision-making process by crowd-voting your content on WeeAct. ● Use our 5-star rating system to rate each other's decisions based on the success or failure of the outcome. ● Increase your vote totals by sharing your WeeAct campaigns on different social networks. ● WeeAct is committed to protecting all user data on our application. We do not sell or share any user data with third parties. The Human Intelligence App: WeeAct has been designed to take advantage of human intelligence by eliminating biases that exist within the crowd. Each voter is ambiguous to the decision-maker, which allows people to vote, honestly, based on their own experiences with that decision. The crowd becomes smarter as more votes are cast on any single decision by eliminating these biases. If life is just a series of decisions, WeeAct is too valuable of a utility not to use. If you struggle to make decisions, WeeAct will revolutionize your life. Download our app for free today and start making smarter decisions . . . together. Got feedback? Send us a message at info@weeact.com. Check out our social media on Twitter and Instagram @WeeActApp
2018_description:
WeeAct is a new decision-making social network that helps users make smarter decisions by harnessing the power of crowd-voting and decision-sharing. Users create campaigns by presenting two options for decisions they face. Other users vote on those campaigns, giving their opinion on which choice is best.

When ready to make a decision based on the crowd-voting, the campaign creator sends out video or photo content to everyone who voted to show them the outcome. Create powerful decision networks where you're influencing others to follow through on their decisions. Life is a series of decisions and WeeAct is the coolest place to crowd-vote digital storytelling content.

Launch a WeeAct campaign around your next Instagram post, your next YouTube video, or which Tinder match you should go on a date with. Not sure which topic to blog about next? Ask your audience using WeeAct.

Follow us on social media, on Twitter @WeeActApp and sign up for our Beta Launch on our homepage, www.weeact.com.

If you struggle to make decisions, WeeAct will revolutionize your life.

2023_description: Meet MyLibrarian—the modern way to browse for books. MyLibrarian is a ML/AI book discovery product that uses big data and expert librarian brains to disrupt a $40B industry. Let our MyLibrarian app and the Librarian Brain book recommendation engine find your next read for you. Booklovers join other readers on our librarian-curated platform, where they can join a freemium community or subscribe to be a part of our monthly book club. Currently in private beta, MyLibrarian / In the Stacks offers recommendation products, from a Librarian Brain database, with the power to suggest books using data-driven systems and expert human-curated data sets, providing the user with pleasantly surprising results.
2018_description:
Currently in private beta, In the Stacks (aka ITS) offers book recommendation apps and subscription products, powered by a Librarian Brain. 2023_description: Compass Therapeutics, Inc. is a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company, developing antibody therapeutics to treat both solid tumors and hematologic malignancies. Compass is leveraging its proprietary StitchMabs™ and common light-chain enabled multispecific platforms to empirically identify multispecifics and combinations of antibody therapeutics that can be advanced to the clinic. The company's lead product candidate, CTX-009, is a bispecific antibody, which inhibits both DLL4-mediated Notch signaling and VEGF-A signaling. CTX-009 has completed a Phase 1 dose escalation study and is in a Phase 1b study in combination with chemotherapy in patients with solid tumors. The company’s second product candidate, CTX-471, is a novel agonistic antibody of CD137, a co-stimulatory receptor on immune cells. It is currently being evaluated in a Phase 1b study in patients who were previously treated with PD-1/PD-L1 checkpoint inhibitors, and who subsequently relapsed or progressed after a period of stable disease. Compass’ third product candidate, CTX-8371, is a bispecific antibody that blocks both PD-1 and PD-L1 and is in IND-enabling studies. The company was founded in 2014 and is headquartered in Boston, Massachusetts.
2018_description:
Compass Therapeutics is a biopharmaceutical company focused on drugging the immune system to treat human diseases.  Using its proprietary antibody discovery and screening platforms, Compass has generated a portfolio of next generation immunomodulatory biologic drug candidates, drug combinations, and multispecifics addressing unmet medical needs in oncology, autoimmunity and other diseases. The company is privately held and completed $83M in Series A financing led by OrbiMed Advisors, F-Prime Capital, Borealis Ventures, Cowen Private Investment, Alexandria Real Estate Ventures and Thiel Capital. 

To learn more, visit www.compasstherapeutics.com

2023_description: The Peak Beyond, a developer of interactive retail solutions in San Rafael, CA, utilizes their proprietary object recognition technology to create smart stores and interactive visual merchandising displays within the retail industries for cannabis, fashion, spirits, and more. Their displays engage and educate consumers, collect consumer behavior data, capture sales, and eliminate customer wait times. The Peak Beyond’s vision is to revolutionize the way that retail is executed. The company’s smart displays use object recognition and touch screen technology to create educational experiences when customers interact with physical products.  The company is working to create a stronghold in the US market by offering two separate products for brands and retailers. The Peak Beyond witnesses sales increases of 40% in smart stores, and 60% with their branded visual merchandising displays.  The Peak Beyond’s products address issues like visibility for brands, operational costs for retailers, and education for consumers. The Peak Beyond’s interactive smart displays solve these problems by reducing staffing costs by 20%, eliminating lines, educating consumers, telling brand stories, allowing point-of-sale marketing and self-checkout, all while increasing average customer spend.  The Peak Beyond has carefully chosen it’s referral partners, building relationships with individuals who are well-connected in various industries. This strategy has allowed TPB to focus on acquiring large-value contracts at low cost. After funding, TPB will hire a sales director and business development director who will manage direct and indirect sales, including outreach to clients in emerging markets, current clients with multiple licenses, and multi-state operators. The Peak Beyond has deployed 150 displays in a variety of use cases including smart stores, express check out, branded merchandising displays, and mobile sales units. They have reached cashflow positive with $32K MRR and have brought in $345K YTD, a 6x growth from 2018.  Their team is well positioned to move forward to create the future of retail. Canopy Boulder SF chose The Peak Beyond as a top company in their accelerator program due their existing traction, their scalability, and their team. They have made worldwide connections in several industries and have received invitations to collaborate and partner with industry leaders in beer, wine, and supplements.  The Peak Beyond has raised $775K and is out to raise $1.5M.

2023_description: Confluent offers a streaming platform based on Apache Kafka that enables companies to easily access data as real-time streams. The company's platform offers an open-source technology that acts as a real-time, fault-tolerant and highly scalable messaging system, enabling companies to move data from isolated systems into a real-time data pipeline where they can act on it immediately.
2018_description:
Confluent offers a real-time data platform built around Apache Kafka.

Apache Kafka, an open source technology created by the founders of Confluent, acts as a real-time, fault tolerant, highly scalable messaging system. It is widely adopted for use cases ranging from collecting user activity data, logs, application metrics, stock ticker data, and device instrumentation. It's key strength is its ability to make high volume data available as a real-time stream for consumption in systems with very different requirements—from batch systems like Hadoop, to realtime systems that require low-latency access, to stream processing engines that transform the data streams as it arrives.

This infrastructure lets you build around a single central nervous system transmitting messages to all the different systems and applications within your company.

2023_description: Axiom Space is the builder, owner, and operator of the commercial space station modules connected to the International Space Station (ISS). 2018_description:
Axiom Space is a Houston-based commercial space startup that seeks to develop the world’s first private commercial space station. It is on a mission to make living and working in Earth orbit commonplace as a means to sustained deep space exploration.

Axiom’s international commercial space station will stimulate growth of the low Earth orbit (LEO) user community by providing additional and expanded services at ISS and allowing a seamless transition to the Axiom station when ISS is retired.  This Axiom Space commercial initiative will allow NASA to realize their mandate to transition the multibillion-dollar LEO market to the private sector. 

With multiple decades of experience as industry leaders in human spaceflight, the Axiom team is confident that they are qualified to ensure continuity and growth for the programs that have been reliant on the ISS, while building and safely operating a multi-user platform that will serve the accelerating demand for human participation in and the industrialization of Space.
