2023_description: Taking one-size-fits-all approach towards health and well-being more often than not will not work. Inlivo is a fully-fledged personalized nutrition platform that helps people uncover and treat nutritional imbalances in their diet, so they can successfully prevent or manage chronic conditions.  In a nutshell, Inlivo works like a fuel gauge for your nutrition – it lets you find out what key vitamins and minerals are missing from your diet, so you can achieve optimal energy, health and performance. Inlivo also provides algorithmically generated wellness plans and real-time coaching customized to each customer's unique body needs and health challenges.  Why we built Inlivo?  It needed to be done. According to research, nutritional imbalances are root cause for many diseases and health problems. According to research, the lack of micro-nutrients (vitamins and minerals) leads to the destruction of DNA, which in turn triggers many health conditions and diseases. Until Inlivo, nobody had tried to tackle the problem of creating an inexpensive real-time method for measuring multiple vitamins and minerals at once. Our AI-based system analyzes millions of data points to provide a simple and elegant solution that offers unique insights about overall diet quality and possible nutritional imbalances.  Inlivo can particularly make a great impact on managing diabetes as it allows for observing trends not only between single foods/meals and glucose levels, but also,  more importantly, between the composition of an entire diet and glucose levels. Patients can identify and treat nutritional deficiencies and potentially improve insulin sensitivity and glucose control.

2023_description: ParkiFi is making parking less of a hassle with their real-time parking occupancy and payment platform. Approximately one out of three cars on the road in downtown Denver is actively looking for a parking spot. Finding that spot takes an average of fifteen minutes of avoidable driving. It was created to take this stress out of people’s lives and reduce the environmental impact of driving. With the ParkiFi app, users simply input an address into the real-time parking map and the app’s parking spot finder directs them to open spaces in garages and lots and automatically allows users to pay for parking via the app at select locations. Metered street parking will be added in 2017. The iOS and Android app launched in downtown Denver in November 2016 and will roll out in other Denver neighborhoods and nationwide in 2017. ParkiFi was recognized as a 2016 “Denver Gazelles” company by the Denver Office of Economic Development.  The company has raised $13.5 million in venture capital to-date. To learn more, visit www.parkifi.com and follow ParkiFi on Facebook, Instagram, and Twitter. It is a Denver-based technology company founded in 2014 by Ryan Sullivan and Rishi Malik in response to a critical insight into downtown traffic.

2023_description: ScreenPay is an app that pays you to get advertisements based on your personal interests and lifestyle right on your phone's lockscreen. The company has developed the technology to serve content, ads, and promotions programatically to Android users lock screen. Once the user unlocks the phone, the ad disappears so it does not interfere with the user’s ability to make calls or take other actions. The ads that are served are relevant to the individual user based on demographic information that they provide to them or that they get when a user logs-in via Facebook Connect. The company will get its install base by paying users a monthly fee to allow them to have this ad on their lock screen. The more demographic information they provide to the company, the more money the user can make. The business model is arbitrage the gross ad revenue they make off of each user against what they pay out to the user. As of February 1, 2014 the build of the app is completed and going through QA prior to the beta release.

2023_description: Scaled Biolabs is pioneering a Cell Therapy Discovery Engine, working at the frontier of microfluidics, automation, and machine learning to develop best-in-class cell-based medicines. This engine enables leading biotech and pharma companies to survey hundreds of parameters across tens of thousands of experimental processes, providing an unprecedented window into cell-driven biology. This enables the development of novel and optimal cell-based products and processes, simplifying manufacturing, reducing time to market, and improving clinical outcomes.  Scaled Biolabs also develops cell therapy assets internally, including a CIRM-funded program focusing on iPSC-derived dopaminergic neurons as a curative cell therapy for Parkinson’s disease.
2018_description: Scaled Biolabs accelerates discovery and translation of cell therapies, to improve quality of life through regenerative medicine. Scaled Biolabs' core technology uses a miniaturized cell culture lab which runs nearly 10,000 experiments in parallel, and an advanced bioinformatics platform that turns single-cell resolution data into deep biological insight. Scaled Biolabs uses this optimization engine to relieve the R&D bottlenecks of companies bringing on complex, advanced medicines such as cell therapies.

Exabeam was the first to put AI and machine learning in its products to deliver behavioral analytics on top of SIEM. 2018_description:
Exabeam is a big data security analytics company that provides enterprises with advanced user behavior intelligence to unlock the potential of existing security information and event management (SIEM) and log management data repositories, enabling IT security teams to more quickly detect and respond to cyberattacks and insider threats in real time. The company’s user behavior intelligence technology fundamentally changes the way cyberattacks are detected and simplifies security operations by focusing on attacker behavior rather than ever-changing malware and tools, shining a spotlight on suspicious network activity and reducing the noise of false positive security alerts. Through extraction and enrichment of log feeds, user session tracking, behavior analysis and event risk scoring, Exabeam gives IT security teams the ability to detect and track credential use in all parts of the attack chain and prioritize responses.

The company was built by seasoned security and enterprise IT veterans from Splunk, Imperva and Sumo Logic, and believes in working together as a team to achieve customer success. To learn more about our corporate culture, visit http://exabeam.com/who-we-are/.

2023_description: Hemlane is a nationwide property management platform. They empower rental owners to manage their properties remotely with a transparent solution that offers online tools and connections to maintenance coordinators and local support. For agents and managers, they can manage existing clients and meet new clients directly on Hemlane. Top features: (1) Rental Marketing: Advertises rentals to over 30 rental listing websites. (2) Show Scheduling: Responds to prospective tenants’ inquiries, schedules showings, and sends reminders to prospective tenants. (3) Applicant Screening: Recommends whether to accept or deny applicants based on objective criteria and comprehensive applications and screening. CleanTalk uses protection methods which are invisible for site visitors. CleanTalk allows you to automate protection against distributed from spam and registration spam bots.  CleanTalk provides reliable protection from attacks and spam bots and promotes strengthening information security throughout the world.  CleanTalk seeks to provide reliable protection, thus contributing to strengthening information security in the world. Nowadays CleanTalk is generally recognized by users who say CleanTalk is one of the best anti-spam services. Spam FireWall CleanTalk has got an advanced option ''Spam FireWall'', this option allows blocking the most active spam bots before they get access to web site. Therefore Spam FireWall significantly can reduce the load on your web server. SpamFireWall can mitigate HTTP/HTTPS DDoS attacks. SpamFireWall can mitigate XML-RPS brute force attacks. About Green Bits:
Green Bits is a retail management and point-of-sale platform that helps legal cannabis retailers grow their businesses.  Green Bits serves more than 750 cannabis retailers in 7 states – Alaska, California, Colorado, Maryland, Nevada, Oregon and Washington – with nearly $2 billion in annual sales processed through the Green Bits point-of-sale.  The company was founded in 2014 and has offices in San Jose, California, and Portland, Oregon.

2023_description: StartBlox is an ecosystem framework for founder teams starting a business and also for catalyst organizations supporting them.  For founder teams using our setup mode, they can follow a series of wizards and resources connections (''blox'') covering 300+ topics, guiding them through planning and researching their business idea, legally forming and registering their company, and establishing critical administrative foundations like accounting, marketing, and HR.  Then in the counterpart ops (operations) mode, users can manage their vendors, expenses, and due dates they set up. For organizations (including franchisors), we offer a white-label version that can be fully branded by the client, including customization of all content and resources.  This could be incubation/acceleration programs or franchise playbooks.  The administrator tools include user management, setup progress views, announcements/event notifications, and chat.

Along the path, users have project management tools including task management, embedded notes, and business templates.  Over time, the environment will grow its community for providing peer-to-peer advice.

StartBlox can also directly connect users to relevant outsource service providers and vendors - locally and nationally - in over a hundred different fields through our partnership with the Better Business Bureau (BBB).

2023_description: Framebridge is a custom framing startup that provides an online custom framing service. The company has tackled the painful, inconvenient and costly process of custom framing an item, replacing it with an experience that places the customer first. Through a tech-forward experience and an obsessive focus on quality and materials, they have introduced a new generation of customers to the tradition of custom manufacturing. Framebridge customers can choose from a curated selection of on-trend frame styles, then upload their photos to the Framebridge website, or ship their items directly to Framebridge in prepaid packaging. The expert team at Framebridge will receive their items and handcraft beautiful custom frames to each customer's exact specifications. The finished pieces ship directly to consumers, arriving in days, ready to hang. Framebridge's transparent pricing, which is determined by the size of each item, begins at $39 and includes free shipping. Framebridge launched in 2014 as a solution to founder Susan Tynan’s ongoing frustration over getting her travel art custom framed. Framebridge investors include New Enterprise Associates (NEA), Revolution Ventures, and SWaN & Legend Venture Partners, as well as seasoned retail and technology executives with industry experience at Crate & Barrel, Rent the Runway, and LivingSocial. The company is headquartered in Washington, DC and operates manufacturing facilities in Richmond, KY, and Lanham, MD.

2023_description: Juvenescence Limited is a British Virgin Islands-based holding company that invests in human aging and longevity. Juvenescence has raised $111M to build an ecosystem and pipeline of assets targeting aging, age-related disease, and regeneration. Juvenescence believes that recent scientific and medical advances will enable the development of therapeutics that meaningfully extend human healthspan and eventually lifespan. A meaningful increase in lifespan in the already aging world will have profound implications on all sectors of society, and in particular healthcare, education, insurance, and leisure. The company creates and partners with new companies with longevity-related therapeutics, by in-licensing compounds from academia and industry, or forming joint ventures with the foremost longevity scientists and leading research institutions. Their work is based on a novel scientific understanding of the underlying biological causes of aging, to create evidence-based therapeutics that can treat diseases of aging. Juvenescence's goal is to extend both lifespan and healthspan, by developing therapeutics that slow aging and promote juvenescence.

2023_description: Augment Marketing was founded by Brian Newmark a veteran of the digital marketing industry. Augment specializes in helping companies develop and build value around their digital media footprint and believes that footprint should be treated as an asset which provides value to a brand. Through our protected process of data analysis, industry trends, benchmarking and global brand analytical reporting and research tools, Augment develops a unique underwriting and rating platform.  The marketplace currently has no set of standards, or risk analysis mechanism's for a company’s digital, social media outlets and content. The lack of these standards increases risk and valuation uncertainty to corporations, financial institutions and capital markets. 2023_description: Third Insight develops patented artificial intelligence (AI) that emulates the human reasoning process, integrating sensor fusion and knowledge-based problem solving to address the needs of both commercial and government customers. Our current projects include AI-based planning and navigation for unmanned aerial and ground vehicles (UAVs, UGVs) in cluttered and/or GPS-denied environments and neuro-symbolic techniques that integrate deep learning with human-readable knowledge bases. Our customers include commercial partners, as well as the Departments of Defense (DOD) and Homeland Security (DHS). Applications of our platform for these customers include aircraft inspection, search and rescue efforts, and warfighter initiatives. We also support the USAF through the development of UAV-based environmental assessments. These techniques utilize deep learning and massive volumes of sensor data (optical, hyperspectral, LIDAR) to create tree species-specific maps of environmental health, which in turn facilitate DOD forest management. Third Insight has over 100 years of cumulative experience spread out across our 10-person team composed of deep learning specialists, software engineers, and hardware experts.
2018_description:
Third Insight is a software development company for drones. It creates software for both defense and consumer-focused companies that serve the drone, Augmented Reality (AR), and surveillance markets. Its patent-pending approach integrates deep learning (for object detection, recognition, and tracking) and graph-network algorithms (for on-line learning and inference) to perform real-time decision making based on context. Its drone platform uses full-scene understanding to solve problems, plan routes, and learn about its environment.

Third Insight gives drones the ability to react more quickly to unexpected events around them. It also enables them to plan and execute complex actions that leverage super-human predictive intelligence.

As an NVIDIA Partner and member of its Inception Program, we have optimized both our computer vision and graph analytics for GPU-accelerated cloud and edge devices, such as the Jetson TX2. Our software integrates with consumer & commercial drone manufacturers as a "plug-and-play" hardware module for customers that want a quick, but full-featured AI solution.

A few of our recent successes: Invited by the Department of Homeland Security, CIT and TechNexus to join their EMERGE 2016 program for startups building wearable technologies for first responders. Proud to be an NVIDIA partner and one of the first companies that NVIDIA has invited to join its "Inception Program" for startups focused on Artificial Intelligence. Selected to join the Capital Factory Accelerator Program in Austin, TX, where the company now resides.

Our software integrates with consumer & commercial drone manufacturers as a "plug-and-play" hardware module for customers that want a quick, but full-featured AI solution.

A few of our recent successes: Invited by the Department of Homeland Security, CIT and TechNexus to join their EMERGE 2016 program for startups building wearable technologies for first responders. Proud to be an NVIDIA partner and one of the first companies that NVIDIA has invited to join its "Inception Program" for startups focused on Artificial Intelligence. Selected to join the Capital Factory Accelerator Program in Austin, TX, where the company now resides.

2023_description:

 Third Insight develops patented artificial intelligence (AI) that emulates the human reasoning process, integrating sensor fusion and knowledge-based problem solving to address the needs of both commercial and government customers. Our customers include commercial partners, as well as the Departments of Defense (DOD) and Homeland Security (DHS). Applications of our platform for these customers include aircraft inspection, search and rescue efforts, and warfighter initiatives. 2023_description: FORTË enables fitness brands globally to create a high-quality, premium digital fitness platform cost-effectively. 2018_description:
FORTË is a tech company (b2b), and a subscription based fitness streaming platform (b2c). We have built hardware and software that we install in a studio so they can seamlessly stream live classes directly to our platform. We are creating a Netflix-style hub of leading boutique fitness studio classes worldwide. Right now a boutique fitness studio is confined to the 30 people or so that can attend their class, but with streaming the entire world can be their audience.

In order to connect the remote users to the in-studio participants we will be curating all wearables on the market to create a live leaderboard. Users will be able to track their performance in real-time, monitor their overall and personal achievements on our social, interactive, and fully immersive platform.

Each studio is outfitted with multiple cameras. The switching of the cameras is fully automated, as well as the audio. We live stream all day from both coasts, with no one operating the streams successfully daily.

2023_description: Bevv allows brewers and cideries to sell directly to the consumer and lets the producer have an online beer/cider presence. Bevv helps you reach new beer and cider enthusiasts outside of your distribution channels. Think of Bevv as a NEW sales channel alongside your current ones. If you are selling beer/cider to-go why wouldn't you use Bevv.com? It's the same process.
2018_description:
Bevv allows brewers to sell directly to the consumer and lets the brewer have an online beer presence. Bevv helps you reach new imbibers outside of your distribution channels. Think of Bevv as a NEW sales channel alongside your current ones. If you are selling beer to-go why wouldn't you use Bevv? It's the same process.

Bevv is a marketplace for the craft beer and craft alcohol industry. Bevv focuses on producer-to-end-user sales within the direct-to-consumer market, bypassing the antiquated, three-tier distribution model increasing margins by 55%. Buyers can purchase directly from producers in turn supporting their favorite brewers / producers. Don't limit your SKU sales to only shelf space items. Vendors can list them all on Bevv.co.

Bevv operates within the confines of each of the individual state direct-to-consumer sales liquor laws and offers a new sales channel to the alcohol industry. We have partnered with key logistics players, payment processing companies and industry influencers to have brought Bevv to fruition. 

We are disrupting the direct-to-consumer alcohol sales marketplace to afford producers business growth. The current market deprives the consumer access to a vast majority of the actual product being produced.

In turn, Bevv is providing an alternative to the near-century-old three-tier distribution model by offering a surrogate to the antiquated alcohol infrastructure. 

Bevv.co
http://bevvshop.tumblr.com/
https://twitter.com/bevvshop

2023_description: MyPostcard is an Android, iOS and website compatible app which allows users to send their own photos as printed postcards or greeting cards worldwide. It offers a range of other customizable products from photo prints to the all-exclusive personalizable audio card, the first on-demand product of its kind. Available in 10 languages, the app is truly international.  The company was founded by CEO Oliver Kray in 2014 in Berlin, Germany. Since then, MyPostcard has grown rapidly and is now the #1 postcard app in Germany and among the most popular across Europe with over 5 million downloads worldwide and a rating of 4.7 stars. August - October 2016: MyPostcard takes part in ''The German Accelerator'' in New York City, as well as Facebook's Incubator FbStart program.  September 2017: MyPostcard acquires the ''Postcard On The Run'' website, a postcard app that became famous in 2013 through Shark Tank and their US investor Robert Herjavec. December 2018: Deutsche Post AG in Germany and MyPostcard reach a major cooperation deal to acquire the customers of the former postcard app, ''FUNCARD''.  Since then, MyPostcard and Deutsche Post AG have been working together successfully. November 2019: MyPostcard is honored with the Deloitte Technology Fast 50 Award in Germany.  The competition honors the 50 fastest-growing technology companies in Germany, measured by their percentage revenue growth. March 2020: MyPostcard ranks 347th (place 19 in the Ecommerce category) in the Financial Times' FT 1000 - distinguishing the company as one of Europe's fastest growing companies.  The Financial Times works with Statista to rank the 1000 biggest, predominantly tech-based companies, with the highest turnover growth percentage in Europe. May 2020: Deutsche Post and MyPostcard partner again to launch DeineBriefmarke.de, the platform that allows private users to create individual, personalized stamps, as well as license holders to create sets of branded stamps. Among these are Benjamin Blümchen and Bibi&Tina; the Van Gogh Museum in Amsterdam; artists including Ruthe; musicians like the Amigos; Leipzig, as the first German town; and organizations like AllOut. June 2020:  MyPostcars wins the German Stevie Award in the Company of the Year 2020 category for media and entertainment.  The Stevie Awards aim to recognize outstanding achievements of companies and experts around the world and have become highly regarded by businesses the world over. October 2020: MyPostcard wins 119 place in the FOCUS BUSINESS Wachstumschampions 2021. The annual ranking by Focus in collaboration with Statista selects the 500 fastest-growing German companies, recognizing their achievements and role in providing jobs and economic stimuli. In the category ‘Newcomer of the Year', MyPostcard also takes home the coveted Licensing International Germany Award 2020. Josipa Gelo, Senior Marketing Manager at MyPostcard, is also awarded the Rising Star award of the licensing industry. Licensing International aim to strengthen the importance of the international licensing industry and to actively communicate its interests to third parties on behalf of its members. December 2020: For the second time in a row, MyPostcard receives the Deloitte Technology Fast 50 Award. March 2021: MyPostcard is listed in the Financial Times 2021 ranking for the second year, making it one of the fastest growing 1000 businesses in Europe according to the Financial Times and Statista. At the German Stevie Awards 2021 this month, MyPostcard also takes home the Gold Status in the category of Fastest Growing Technology Company of the Year, along with the Bronze Award for Company of the Year 2021. November 2021: In the 2021 Focus Growth Champions, MyPostcard ranks 32nd, making it once again, one of Germany’s fastest-growing companies according to Focus and Statista.  MyPostcard also wins the Gold Globee® in the 8th Annual 2021 International Best in Business Awards. For the third year in a row, MyPostcard receives the Deloitte Technology Fast 50 Award, ranking 37th. MyPostcard’s marketing concept places among the top 10 nominees at the German Marketing Award 2021.

2023_description: GiveBack360 is a cloud-based cause marketing platform that blends for-profit strategies with non-profit fundraising. The features of the system drive fundraising from purchases, deliver instant giving solutions to local businesses as partners within their communities and connect individuals to an automatic way to support the schools and nonprofits they care about.  GiveBack360's mission is to facilitate everyone's opportunity to give back through ''Save & Give Offers''.  Individuals save money on a product or service and simultaneously donate to their favorite cause with every purchase. Nonprofits are at the core of GiveBack360's business model and they are provided with socially driven fundraising tools and solutions at no cost!  All nonprofits have instant access to the world's first ''60 second fundraiser''.  GiveBack360 has eliminated any barrier to participation in the network by providing free registration to members, nonprofits, schools and merchants. The vision has been crystallized as  Philanthropy Reimagined®; A Virtuous Circle of Giving Where Everyone Wins.  To learn more about this organization visit the website: www.giveback360.com Also find us on Facebook & Twitter:  www.facebook.com/giveback360 www.twitter.com/giveback360

2023_description: Expa is a startup studio and venture fund designed for entrepreneurs to create and launch new companies. Started in 2013 by Uber co-founder Garrett Camp, Expa is a team of experienced founders and entrepreneurs dedicated to identifying the next big idea and partnering with the future generation of leaders to build great companies. Our partners have founded or led some of the most valuable and well-known companies including Uber, Twitter, LinkedIn, FourSquare, StumbleUpon, AddThis, MetroLyrics, and Envoy.  Expa has raised $350 million from a number of investors including Expa Founder/CEO Garrett Camp and other LPs.
2018_description:
Expa is a global network of entrepreneurs helping each other build companies.

Founded in 2013, the company partners with proven founders to create new products and services and build teams to launch them as independent companies. Expa typically founds new companies based on their own ideas, though occasionally collaborates with founders of early-state companies.

Expa was founded by Garrett Camp, co-founder of Uber and StumbleUpon, to apply his lessons learned creating successful startups. Joined by Hooman Radfar (founder of AddThis), Naveen Selvadurai (Foursquare co-founder), Milun Tesovic (founder of Metrolyrics), Roberto Sanabria (Google, Linkedin), Vítor Lourenço (Twitter designer, co-founder of Envoy) and 25 talented in-house experts in SF & NYC, the Expa team actively guides companies.

2023_description: All the work that an engineer does is largely forgotten after said feature, product, or fix has been released. We are a small group of software engineers who believe that this should not be the case. We believe an engineer’s work can tell a story. This work, from commits and source code contains a wealth of information not only immediately valuable for ourselves but also to the larger engineering community to share, discuss, and most importantly learn from. After all, all software engineers ultimately do is write and commit code. Our commits and source code have it all: the languages and libraries we use, how much we show off by using fancy language features, what math we like, who we work with, how much we loath unit tests, and how brave we are to refactor. We want our work to speak for us and so created Sourcerer. 2023_description: RolloDecks updates your contact card on other people's mobile devices anytime you make a change. You can provide different contact cards to different groups of people. Your contacts don't need the RolloDecks app to receive updates due to our proprietary''app-less'' mode. 2023_description: Carista is an Android app that lets you check your vehicle for problems, as well as clear any existing fault codes.  Carista can check your vehicle's health and report any faults stored its computers. Unlike other apps, Carista gives you access to advanced manufacturer-specific diagnostics, including computers like ABS, airbag, navigation, etc. You can also clear any fault codes and reset your check engine light, airbag light, ABS light, traction control light, etc.  Carista's overheat alarm (a paid feature, 99 cents) allows you to monitor your engine's temperature and react early if it starts to overheat. Carista can run in the background and notify you with an alarm sound right when the engine temperature starts to reach dangerous levels.
2018_description:
Carista is an Android app that lets you check your vehicle for problems, as well as clear any existing fault codes. You can also customize your car to your liking! Carista is compatible with standard (i.e. inexpensive) ELM327 Bluetooth adapters that plug into your vehicle's diagnostic OBD2 port. 

Carista can check your vehicle's health and report any faults stored its computers. Unlike other apps, Carista gives you access to advanced manufacturer-specific diagnostics, including computers like ABS, airbag, navigation, etc. You can also clear any fault codes and reset your check engine light, airbag light, ABS light, traction control light, etc. 

Carista lets you change the way your car behaves: say you want your headlights to come on automatically when you start the engine; or you want the doors to lock when you start moving; or you want to change the type of beep that the reverse parking sensors make. Yes, Carista can do that (if your vehicle supports it, of course).

Carista's overheat alarm (a paid feature, 99 cents) allows you to monitor your engine's temperature and react early if it starts to overheat. Carista can run in the background and notify you with an alarm sound right when the engine temperature starts to reach dangerous levels.

Published results show Shoulder Innovations’ solution provides greater post-surgical implant stability, addressing the leading cause of revision surgery.

2023_description: Zeto is a commercial stage medical technology startup transforming the way EEG (Electroencephalography) is done at hospitals. We are solving a problem unsolved since EEG was invented in 1924, i.e., an archaic, tedious approach that consumes time, requires a trained technician and puts the patient through a poor experience. Our product is the first FDA cleared wireless, zero-prep, easy-to-wear headset with dry electrodes. The device is backed by a digital platform that offers instant upload, tools for analysis, and remote interpretation by neurologists. A process that takes over 30 mins by a technician just to set up will instead take just 5 minutes from putting on the headset to interpretable EEG. Zeto has won several awards including $350,000 from the Epilepsy Foundation, 2018 MedTech Innovator Showcase company, 2018 Exponential Medicine MEDY Outstanding Pitch Award, 2017 Rosenman Innovator by UCSF's QB3.

2023_description: Suiteness is a luxury travel startup, with an online booking platform that lets users access an inventory of suites, penthouses, and villas from luxury hotels. It also offers rooms that connect to suites for half the price of a typical two-bedroom suite for groups of 4 or more.  With access to the most luxurious suites, most of which have never been offered online before, guests experience amenities like private entrances, personal butlers, and even private pools. In addition to luxury travelers, the service is intended for families and large groups looking for accommodations with multiple bedrooms and shared space as the website carries exclusive suites with one to five attached bedrooms. Suiteness focuses on the hotel side as well by providing partners with brand protection, visibility, data transparency, and flexibility. The ultimate goal of the company is to showcase and market their hotel partners' most prized inventory, services, brand, and amenities through a unique and exciting platform.  Currently, Suiteness is live in Las Vegas, New York, Miami, Orlando, Los Angeles, and London with access to luxury suites, half of which are being offered exclusively through Suiteness. The company intends to expand rapidly this year. They are headquartered in Oakland, CA. Suiteness was a part of Y Combinator's Summer 2016 class and in 2015, the company received investments from Structure Capital and Keystone Capital. In December 2016, Suiteness raised $5 million in a Series A round of funding, led by Bullpen Capital and Global Founders Capital and including participation from Max Levchin's HVF fund, Kima Ventures and Altair Capital.

2023_description: WiFi Security is a growing threat to small and large businesses. Hackers can steal information from you and your customers from your WiFi and their presence may even damage your reputation as a business. By adding Prowl's security layer, you can have peace of mind that our preinstalled security features, such as Hoosegow, will trap malicious activity (port scanning, DDoS, bandwidth consumption) and discard/stop it accordingly.
2018_description:
WiFi Security is a growing threat to small and large businesses. Hackers can steal information from you and your customers from your WiFi and their presence may even damage your reputation. By adding Prowl's security layer, you can have peace of mind that our preinstalled security features, such as Hoosegow, will trap malicious activity and discard it accordingly. Businesses that use Prowl are often recognized for providing secure WiFi. 

Prowl is a startup founded and developed by Montana Mendy. Montana is known for defending Path in some controversy in 2013, also for his Linux work, and other apps he's published. Prowl, along with an extensive software side, has a proprietary hardware backend. Prowl also uses Python, Bonjour, and Django (web framework) to let business owners know what their patrons are listening to, in real time, in which, the owner or manager can make better decisions on what music to play in-store -- or use our "suggestions" that is curated by our own algorithm.

Prowl is located South of Market in San Francisco, California. Prowl's offices are adjacent to Civic Center.

2023_description: AgSmarts is a provider of environmental sensing and agricultural irrigation automation in the agriculture industry. With global demand for agricultural output rising and constraints confronting agricultural producers from all sides of their operations, AgSmarts helps farmers address these challenges by introducing the power of industrial controls. Its universal retrofit irrigation automation platform helps producers boost yields while reducing their operational costs and minimizing their water usage. The company's patent-pending IP-enabled sensing and wireless communication hardware coupled with its proprietary automation algorithms are revolutionizing agriculture by gathering critical environmental data directly from fields that allow existing irrigation infrastructure to anticipate and autonomously meet the soil moisture needs of the specific crop being grown in the field throughout the production season. The technology is distributed through existing Ag Service Providers' retail operations on a Platform as a Service (PaaS) basis and begins immediately improving the producer's bottom line when installed on their existing irrigation equipment through increased yield revenues and lower operational costs. Clayton Plymill and Brett Norman in Martin, Tennessee in 2014.

2023_description: OUR VISION: We are a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization that promotes and provide space systems engineering education and opportunities to high school students in all socioeconomic statuses!  OUR MISSION: Most high schools lack sufficient funds for sponsoring innovation and development of CubeSats.  This impact is felt across the STEM and Aerospace programs of many schools across the United States, disadvantaging ambitious deserving students with bright futures.    The CubeSat Development Education Initiative is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization that promotes and provides space systems engineering opportunities and enrichment to students. We aim to inspire innovation and fulfill the dreams of countless high school students to make their own satellite and pursue careers in Aerospace related industries while emphasizing its economic significance. The CubeSat Development Education Initiative was inspired by our Founder -Brian Kardos- who attempted to develop a CubeSat satellite at his high school and experienced firsthand the many roadblocks to Aerospace education.

2023_description: Northern.tech builds a suite of ease-to-use security products for the connected world. Each product shall not only be a single-purpose product, but also complement each other to give their customers the option to pick and choose the products that best fits their needs. Their products shall address the needs of everyone from small companies to large enterprises - world wide. ***MENDER*** Mender provides a secure and robust over-the-air (OTA) software update management solution for embedded devices and the Internet of Things (connected devices) across horizontal markets. The unique benefits of Mender lies in security and robustness guarantee for devices to stay operational as they receive software updates, a very delicate and nuanced process. Even in case of a devastating event such as sudden power or network loss during an update, Mender will be able to recover and restore the device into a well known good running state. The open core business model offers minimal barriers for embedded and IoT developers to adopt and start using Mender. Mender’s focus on ease of use provides quick time-to-value allowing developers to focus on their product’s core features. ***CFEngine*** CFEngine is a large-scale software solution that helps system administrators and other stakeholders in large IT organizations to become more agile and respond faster to business requirements while ensuring SLAs and regulatory compliance. CFEngine, the inventor of infrastructure-as-code, allows users, in code using the domain specific language (DSL) of CFEngine, to define desired states of their IT infrastructure. Lightweight CFEngine agents continuously ensures that the actual states are converging toward the desired states, and reporting desired and actual states. The solution is built upon Promise Theory(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Promise_theory). Written in C, CFEngine runs on multiple platforms and architectures, from the smallest embedded devices to large servers and mainframes, easily handling tens and hundreds of thousands of resources. Many DevOps organizations use CFEngine to ensure consistency across different environments and automated application deployment. Due to its strong security track-record CFEngine is widely used in regulated industries like financial services, telecom, health care and governmental agencies. The solution comes in a free open source Community Edition and paid commercial Enterprise Edition, also leveraging the open core model.

CFEngine, the inventor of infrastructure-as-code, allows users, in code using the domain specific language (DSL) of CFEngine, to define desired states of their IT infrastructure. Lightweight CFEngine agents continuously ensures that the actual states are converging toward the desired states, and reporting desired and actual states. The solution is built upon Promise Theory(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Promise_theory). Written in C, CFEngine runs on multiple platforms and architectures, from the smallest embedded devices to large servers and mainframes, easily handling tens and hundreds of thousands of resources. Many DevOps organizations use CFEngine to ensure consistency across different environments and automated application deployment. Due to its strong security track-record CFEngine is widely used in regulated industries like financial services, telecom, health care and governmental agencies. The solution comes in a free open source Community Edition and paid commercial Enterprise Edition, also leveraging the open core model.
